<br>
Recommended: Elemental Pact (if possible; otherwise a Reagent Conservation 3 item), Right-click Reclaim Energy item (Such as a standard Shovel of Ponz), specialization in Conjuration<br>
<br>
Works like this: Summon a MS2 pet, reclaim, repeat. The result? Fast mana regeneration (I was getting roughly 6% per summon).<br>
<br>
The downside? Mod rodding might result in faster mana regen (can't check, as i'm not 56). No usable pet during this process. Without Elemental Pact, you burn through a LOT of malachite.<br>
<br>
But it works damnit! Its also a major relief on the clerics/healers from having to heal you from all that mod-rodding. :) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xalmat>Xalmat</A> at: 8/14/02 11:53:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=11yadin11>11yadin11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(8/15/02 2:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1479.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: One mage's solution to fast mana regen</span><hr size=1> Modding is faster, and that gets kinda pricey but I supose with Elemental pact it wouldnt cost anything and it would also save your HP. Maybe a way to get more mana while resting from rods, even better if your on a horse. The major draw backs would be the lack of pet during the mana regen and the amount of malachite( if you need it ) to make it effective. Oh yea and the dreaded re-peting and re-buffing... Im forgeting something.... oh yea the time your standing if not on a horsey.<br>
<br>
   IMHO I dont realy think its worth it after you get modrod 2. If you dont have MR2 then id have to say if you can handle the extra malachite more mana is always great.<br>
